{
  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, with regard to effectiveness in eliciting information from respondents, several previous reports noted that chatbot interfaces could be more effective (Xiao et al., 2020a,b) and preferable (te Pas et al., 2020) than surveys.",
    "A reason that could underlie this finding is that there is evidence suggesting that people are more willing to share information through chatbots (Lee et al., 2020), which are generally believed to be useful for collaboration (Kim et al., 2021).",
    "Together with LLMs such as GPT-3, recent research has explored the usability of these models in operating chatbots (Wei et al., 2023).",
    "In line with this novel technology, in the present study, we empirically test a chatbot framework that may be more effective than survey methods for eliciting meaningful responses from participants in the context of urban design.",
    "We developed a chatbot system with dual functionalities to discuss an urban design project."
  ]
}